  "texts": [
    "To further support these arguments, the Pearson correlation between sensitivity and consistency (without said degenerate cases where sensitivity is less than 0.05) has a value of -0.07.",
    "These results agree with our intuitions about the utility of these metrics: a random predictor p τ (y|x) would achieve S τ ≈ 1 but C y ≈ 1, whereas another that always predicts a specific class has S τ ≈ 0 and C y ≈ 1.",
    "All combinations are possible, providing different views about LLMs' behavior.",
    "As a result, developers should pay attention when switching LLMs in their applications: a prompt that worked well with an LLM might cause instability (see the sensitivity gaps on CB) and significantly worse performance on another.",
    "For instance, on CB it might be preferable to choose the Detail strategy with Mixtral, since sensitivity is extremely low and the other metrics are highest compared to the alternative strategies."
